Pour 300ml cold salted water into a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}. Stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, lower the heat to medium, cover with the lid and cook for ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, remove the #pot{} from the heat. Set aside for ~{12%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Trim the @carrot{1%unit}(trimmed and halved lengthways, chopped into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons) and halve lengthways (no need to peel). Place a #large pan{} over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Once hot add the carrot and fry until tender, ~{5-6%minutes}. Meanwhile, halve the @baby corn{150%g} lengthways. Trim and thinly slice the @scallion{1%unit}(trimmed and thinly sliced). Quarter the @lime{1%unit}(quartered).

Reduce the heat of the #pan{} to medium-high. Add the @garlic, ginger & lemongrass paste{1%sachet} and baby corn and fry until fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the @coconut milk{1%pack}, @vegetable stock powder{1%sachet}, @korma curry paste{1%sachet}, @dried chilli flakes{2%sachets} (use less if you don't like spice) and 75ml @water{to taste}. Cover and simmer for ~{4-6%minutes}. When there's ~{1%minute} of cooking time left, add the @peas{120%g} and allow to warm through. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Add a splash of water if you feel it's too thick.

Divide the fragrant rice and curry between #plates{}. Scatter sliced scallion and @peanuts{20%g} over the top. Finish off with a squeeze of lime juice. Serve any remaining lime wedges alongside.